(tribal music playing)

259
00:16:52.720 --> 00:16:56.181
(speaking Dothraki)

260
00:16:56.265 --> 00:16:57.641
Ahh.

261
00:16:59.476 --> 00:17:01.061
He was the love of my life.

262
00:17:01.145 --> 00:17:02.604
(speaking Dothraki)

263
00:17:02.688 --> 00:17:05.232
No. no. not totally.

264
00:17:05.315 --> 00:17:07.901
(speaking Dothraki)

265
00:17:07.984 --> 00:17:11.280
(chuckles) Come on.

266
00:17:15.451 --> 00:17:16.451
(gasps)

267
00:17:19.204 --> 00:17:23.709
- What are you doing?
- (warrior speaking Dothraki)

268
00:17:23.791 --> 00:17:24.917
Okay.

269
00:17:26.086 --> 00:17:27.296
Ah.

270
00:17:27.378 --> 00:17:29.757
(moaning)

271
00:17:38.557 --> 00:17:41.477
Wait. you're telling me
Ethan tore your clothes off

272
00:17:41.560 --> 00:17:43.020
and fucked the shit out of you?

273
00:17:43.103 --> 00:17:45.689
Yeah... it's great.

274
00:17:46.774 --> 00:17:49.651
- Wow.
- Go Ethan!

275
00:17:50.569 --> 00:17:51.612
Bye.

276
00:18:00.996 --> 00:18:03.832
Rue: Nate was released from
the hospital a few days earlier.

277
00:18:14.384 --> 00:18:16.095
Cal: I have a
hard time believing

278
00:18:16.178 --> 00:18:17.971
you don't know
who did this to you.

279
00:18:20.015 --> 00:18:23.352
- Dad. just leave it alone.
- Well. I'm not going to.

280
00:18:25.062 --> 00:18:26.730
Nate: Yeah. well. you should.

281
00:18:30.025 --> 00:18:33.070
Rue: It's one thing
to dislike your parents.

282
00:18:33.153 --> 00:18:35.989
It's not like you have a choice.

283
00:18:36.073 --> 00:18:37.991
But if you dislike your kid...

284
00:18:39.910 --> 00:18:42.329
well. that's sort of your fault.

285
00:18:44.248 --> 00:18:47.543
I just have a hard time
believing it was unprovoked.

286
00:18:47.626 --> 00:18:48.961
He's our son.

287
00:18:50.128 --> 00:18:53.382
I know... I know.
I'm just sayin'.

288
00:18:55.467 --> 00:18:58.679
(Cassie on phone. crying)
I just wanna kill myself.

289
00:18:58.762 --> 00:19:02.224
Rue: As soon as Nate had
been released from the hospital...

290
00:19:02.307 --> 00:19:04.685
he wished he was
back in the hospital.

291
00:19:04.768 --> 00:19:07.104
Just take a deep breath.

292
00:19:07.187 --> 00:19:09.481
Nate. I'm legit going
crazy right now.

293
00:19:09.565 --> 00:19:11.316
You can't do this to me.

294
00:19:12.776 --> 00:19:15.654
- Suze: Lex?
- What?

295
00:19:15.737 --> 00:19:18.198
What's going on
with your sister?

296
00:19:18.282 --> 00:19:20.409
Lexi: I think she's having
a nervous breakdown.

297
00:19:20.492 --> 00:19:22.035
About what?

298
00:19:22.119 --> 00:19:24.788
Lexi: I don't know.
Being single or something.

299
00:19:26.373 --> 00:19:28.208
No...

300
00:19:28.292 --> 00:19:30.752
those aren't the emotions
of a single person.

301
00:19:33.797 --> 00:19:36.300
Rue: The only way Nate was
able to calm Cassie down enough

302
00:19:36.383 --> 00:19:39.428
to stop crying
was to tell her...

303
00:19:39.511 --> 00:19:43.432
I promise we can meet
in person next weekend.

304
00:19:43.515 --> 00:19:46.184
Rue: But then he said something
that totally freaked her out.

305
00:19:46.268 --> 00:19:48.937
(dramatic music playing)

306
00:19:49.021 --> 00:19:50.999
Nate (on phone): If Maddy
finds out. she's gonna spend

307
00:19:51.023 --> 00:19:53.233
the rest of her life
trying to kill me.

308
00:19:53.317 --> 00:19:54.359
I know.

309
00:19:54.443 --> 00:19:56.778
Nate: But she'll
actually kill you.

310
00:19:56.862 --> 00:19:59.865
♪ ♪

311
00:20:01.825 --> 00:20:03.493
Fucking racist.

312
00:20:03.577 --> 00:20:04.828
Ahh!

313
00:20:06.997 --> 00:20:09.625
- Sorry. I didn't hear you. bitch. What?!
- (grunting)

314
00:20:11.835 --> 00:20:15.297
(tense music playing)

315
00:20:15.380 --> 00:20:17.883
♪ ♪

316
00:20:22.554 --> 00:20:25.724
(frantic organ playing)

317
00:20:30.979 --> 00:20:33.315
- Jules: Hey. Cass.
- Cassie: Hey. Jules.

318
00:20:34.942 --> 00:20:36.777
Rue: Now. at the time.
I didn't know how much

319
00:20:36.860 --> 00:20:38.695
the Elliot thing upset Jules.

320
00:20:41.156 --> 00:20:44.159
But I never thought that
Jules was like clingy or jealous.

321
00:20:44.242 --> 00:20:47.079
so I didn't think
it'd be a big deal.

322
00:20:47.162 --> 00:20:49.623
- It is a big deal.
- Why?

323
00:20:49.706 --> 00:20:52.000
The fact that you're even
asking me to explain it to you

324
00:20:52.084 --> 00:20:54.503
- is kind of an even bigger deal.
- Oh. I don't understand

325
00:20:54.586 --> 00:20:56.588
how such a small fucking thing

326
00:20:56.672 --> 00:21:00.634
has become such
a big fucking thing.

327
00:21:00.717 --> 00:21:02.844
- 'Cause it hurt my feelings.
- Rue: Why?

328
00:21:02.928 --> 00:21:05.013
'Cause I can tell you
have a crush on him.

329
00:21:05.097 --> 00:21:07.391
I do not have a
fucking crush on him.

330
00:21:07.474 --> 00:21:09.851
Jules: Then why else would
you forget meeting him?

331
00:21:09.935 --> 00:21:13.522
- Like. "Oh. that's right. New Year's."
- Jules. it's not like that.

332
00:21:13.605 --> 00:21:15.165
- "Silly me."
- Rue: It's not like that.

333
00:21:15.190 --> 00:21:18.860
Well. I hope not.
That would really suck.

334
00:21:18.944 --> 00:21:21.488
- I'm sorry.
- Jules: Um. I gotta be home in 15 minutes.

335
00:21:21.571 --> 00:21:24.491
or else I'm gonna get
grounded for another two weeks.

336
00:21:24.574 --> 00:21:26.326
I'll see ya later. Rue.

337
00:21:28.203 --> 00:21:31.331
- I get you in trouble?
- Yeah. kinda.

338
00:21:33.583 --> 00:21:35.711
I feel like we should do drugs.

339
00:21:35.794 --> 00:21:39.381
(electronica music playing)

340
00:21:39.464 --> 00:21:41.842
♪ Hey. y'all know what's up ♪

341
00:21:51.977 --> 00:21:54.604
Why don't you
have a seat. Cassie?

342
00:21:54.688 --> 00:21:58.525
Mr. Jacobs believes you
know who assaulted his son.

343
00:21:58.608 --> 00:22:01.069
(tense music playing)

344
00:22:01.153 --> 00:22:02.404
(slurps)

345
00:22:02.487 --> 00:22:04.990
Rue: Meanwhile...

346
00:22:05.073 --> 00:22:07.993
Fezco had a new house guest.

347
00:22:08.076 --> 00:22:11.371
Ashtray was so pissed off
he couldn't even speak to Fez.

348
00:22:14.666 --> 00:22:15.876
(sighs)

349
00:22:18.795 --> 00:22:22.466
- Good morning!
- Morning.

350
00:22:22.549 --> 00:22:24.676
Rue: Fezco couldn't
understand the whole story.

351
00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:25.761
(dog barking)

352
00:22:25.844 --> 00:22:27.054
But apparently Faye had pushed

353
00:22:27.137 --> 00:22:28.680
the motel manager
off the balcony.

354
00:22:28.764 --> 00:22:31.558
(manager yelling)

355
00:22:32.934 --> 00:22:35.228
- (dog barking) -
(helicopter hovering)

356
00:22:35.312 --> 00:22:37.314
The fucking cops
are looking for Faye.

357
00:22:37.397 --> 00:22:38.565
What the fuck!

358
00:22:38.648 --> 00:22:40.734
(cries) I. I didn't do anything.

359
00:22:40.817 --> 00:22:43.278
Rue: Unfortunately.
Custer wouldn't leave her.

360
00:22:43.361 --> 00:22:46.573
I know. dude. but
she's the love of my life.

361
00:22:48.825 --> 00:22:50.786
Rue: And the last
thing Fezco needed

362
00:22:50.869 --> 00:22:52.913
was the cops finding
Faye with Custer.

363
00:22:52.996 --> 00:22:55.082
- (whines) - Get
in the fucking vent.

364
00:22:55.165 --> 00:22:57.042
- (banging on door)
- Faye: Ow.

365
00:22:57.125 --> 00:22:59.252
Officer: I know you're
in there. Open up!

366
00:22:59.336 --> 00:23:01.963
-(banging continues) -Custer:
Oh my god. Get in the fucking vent!

367
00:23:02.047 --> 00:23:03.757
I love you.

368
00:23:03.840 --> 00:23:05.467
Rue: Custer told
Fez he could find her

369
00:23:05.550 --> 00:23:08.178
behind the dumpster
of the new Taco Bell.

370
00:23:08.261 --> 00:23:11.765
(rap music playing
on car stereo)

371
00:23:16.478 --> 00:23:18.522
Don't look at me like that.

372
00:23:18.605 --> 00:23:20.398
The only reason
that I went so crazy

373
00:23:20.482 --> 00:23:25.237
is because the motel manager
kept saying such mean things.

374
00:23:25.320 --> 00:23:27.614
I honestly don't give a fuck.

375
00:23:29.616 --> 00:23:31.660
Rue: So Faye
came to live with Fez.

376
00:23:31.743 --> 00:23:34.955
Yo. don't touch nothin'.

377
00:23:35.038 --> 00:23:37.249
- Don't talk to Ash.
- Okay.

378
00:23:37.332 --> 00:23:40.418
And don't go in my
fuckin' room. all right?

379
00:23:41.586 --> 00:23:43.046
I promise.

380
00:23:46.633 --> 00:23:49.970
- Want some of my sandwich?
- Faye: Okay.

381
00:23:52.931 --> 00:23:55.350
Cassie. I asked you a question.

382
00:23:55.433 --> 00:23:57.561
Lexi: She didn't see anything.

383
00:23:57.644 --> 00:24:00.647
I'm not asking
you. I'm asking her.

384
00:24:03.400 --> 00:24:05.861
I already told Mrs. Jacobs
I didn't see anything.

385
00:24:05.944 --> 00:24:08.780
I know. We just
don't believe you.

386
00:24:10.365 --> 00:24:12.742
I'm telling the truth.

387
00:24:12.826 --> 00:24:14.661
Look. Cassie. I'm
more than happy to get

388
00:24:14.744 --> 00:24:17.664
the Chief of Police. Bill
Greenwood. involved.

389
00:24:17.747 --> 00:24:19.666
Old family friend.

390
00:24:19.749 --> 00:24:22.711
Maybe he should have
this conversation with you.

391
00:24:23.712 --> 00:24:26.756
With everyone.
in fact. You know?

392
00:24:28.592 --> 00:24:31.178
Get everyone's cell phones.

393
00:24:31.261 --> 00:24:33.013
Text histories.

394
00:24:33.972 --> 00:24:36.099
Find out what exactly happened.

395
00:24:37.017 --> 00:24:38.727
Should we do that instead?

396
00:24:40.937 --> 00:24:45.442
Rue: Now. what scared
the shit out of Cassie...

397
00:24:45.525 --> 00:24:47.152
was last night she texted Nate.

398
00:24:47.235 --> 00:24:48.653
(text notification)

399
00:24:53.408 --> 00:24:56.077
- (phone ringing)
- Hello?

400
00:24:56.161 --> 00:24:58.663
Nate (on phone): Don't
ever put that in writing again.

401
00:24:59.956 --> 00:25:01.416
I'm sorry.

402
00:25:04.336 --> 00:25:07.255
Don't look at her. Look at me.

403
00:25:11.176 --> 00:25:13.261
- Why would you say that?
- What?!

404
00:25:13.345 --> 00:25:16.097
- What was I supposed to do?
- Not say anything.

405
00:25:16.181 --> 00:25:18.099
You heard him! He was
going to call the police!

406
00:25:18.183 --> 00:25:19.559
No. he wasn't. He was bluffing.

407
00:25:19.643 --> 00:25:21.495
and you fell for it 'cause
you're a fucking idiot!

408
00:25:21.519 --> 00:25:24.898
- Why do you even care?!
- Because you just ruined someone's life!

409
00:25:24.981 --> 00:25:28.818
Fezco almost killed Nate!
That was his decision.

410
00:25:36.493 --> 00:25:38.828
Rue: Lexi had thought
about that night a lot.

411
00:25:38.912 --> 00:25:43.667
How could Fezco be so kind to
her. and so violent towards Nate?

412
00:25:43.750 --> 00:25:46.294
She couldn't remember the last
time someone her age asked her

413
00:25:46.378 --> 00:25:49.256
so many questions about herself.

414
00:25:49.339 --> 00:25:52.634
He actually cared about
what she had to say.

415
00:25:52.717 --> 00:25:54.552
And then. 10 minutes later...

416
00:25:56.012 --> 00:25:59.057
almost beat Nate
Jacobs to death.

417
00:26:00.642 --> 00:26:04.354
And even if Nate deserved
it. it was a horrible thing to do.

418
00:26:08.233 --> 00:26:10.360
It made her think
about her entire life.

419
00:26:13.655 --> 00:26:16.366
How she's always
been so passive.

420
00:26:21.037 --> 00:26:23.832
How she never had the
courage to say anything.

421
00:26:28.086 --> 00:26:31.840
And even the time when she did
get the courage to say something?

422
00:26:31.923 --> 00:26:34.009
Rue. you really
need to get help.

423
00:26:35.427 --> 00:26:37.679
What. are you gonna tell
my mom or something?

424
00:26:37.762 --> 00:26:40.557
Yeah. if you don't stop.

425
00:26:43.476 --> 00:26:45.020
Okay.

426
00:26:46.688 --> 00:26:48.773
- (snorts)
- She backed down.

427
00:26:51.985 --> 00:26:53.570
Suze: Hon...

428
00:26:55.822 --> 00:26:58.158
I don't wanna scare you...

429
00:26:58.241 --> 00:26:59.951
but somethin' happened to Rue.

430
00:27:00.035 --> 00:27:02.871
She's okay. She's okay.

431
00:27:04.247 --> 00:27:06.583
But I think she overdosed.

432
00:27:06.666 --> 00:27:08.960
(somber music playing)

433
00:27:09.044 --> 00:27:10.253
Oh...

434
00:27:11.671 --> 00:27:13.673
Come here. Come here.

435
00:27:17.177 --> 00:27:19.387
(Lexi crying) It's my fault.

436
00:27:22.140 --> 00:27:24.392
Rue: She hated
herself for being so weak

437
00:27:24.476 --> 00:27:26.686
and passive and afraid.

438
00:27:26.770 --> 00:27:29.356
So. a couple of days
after Cal came over.

439
00:27:29.439 --> 00:27:31.441
she decided to say something.

440
00:27:31.524 --> 00:27:35.820
("Haunted" by Laura Les playing)

441
00:27:35.904 --> 00:27:38.865
♪ Yeah. do you think it's
cute that I'm so fucking stupid ♪

442
00:27:38.948 --> 00:27:40.241
♪ Tired of bein' useless ♪

443
00:27:40.325 --> 00:27:41.565
♪ I've been up for three days ♪

444
00:27:41.618 --> 00:27:44.037
♪ Everything is haunted.
everybody's evil ♪

445
00:27:44.120 --> 00:27:46.373
♪ And there's bugs
inside the carpet ♪

446
00:27:46.456 --> 00:27:47.791
♪ Do you think I'm frightening ♪

447
00:27:47.874 --> 00:27:50.335
♪ Organ chords and
lightning. if I show my fangs ♪

448
00:27:50.418 --> 00:27:51.729
♪ Will you tell me
that they're cool ♪

449
00:27:51.753 --> 00:27:53.505
♪ Mirrors shatter
when I'm passing ♪

450
00:27:53.588 --> 00:27:54.839
♪ Broken glass and crashing ♪

451
00:27:54.923 --> 00:27:57.967
♪ Little blurry stars
scattered all across my room ♪

452
00:28:03.890 --> 00:28:05.058
(loads gun)

453
00:28:07.018 --> 00:28:08.770
Rue: Now. I didn't
know any of this

454
00:28:08.853 --> 00:28:12.023
'cause I was with Elliot
smokin' a little bit of weed.

455
00:28:12.107 --> 00:28:14.359
Jules invited me over
to her house for dinner.

456
00:28:14.442 --> 00:28:18.071
I guess like to apologize.
but I had NA that night

457
00:28:18.154 --> 00:28:20.156
so I went to Elliot's for a bit.

458
00:28:20.240 --> 00:28:23.243
♪ Long as I've got your love ♪

459
00:28:23.326 --> 00:28:26.079
♪ You know that
I'll never leave ♪

460
00:28:27.288 --> 00:28:30.250
♪ When I wanted
you to share my life ♪

461
00:28:30.333 --> 00:28:33.628
♪ I had no doubt in my mind ♪

462
00:28:33.711 --> 00:28:38.049
♪ And it's been you. woman ♪

463
00:28:38.133 --> 00:28:41.469
♪ Right down the line ♪

464
00:28:44.472 --> 00:28:49.060
♪ I just wanna say
this is my way ♪

465
00:28:49.144 --> 00:28:52.605
♪ Of tellin' you everything ♪

466
00:28:52.689 --> 00:28:56.025
♪ I could never say before ♪

467
00:28:56.109 --> 00:28:58.194
♪ ♪

468
00:28:59.362 --> 00:29:00.989
(knock on door)

469
00:29:01.072 --> 00:29:04.200
David: Should I just put dinner
in the oven till Rue gets here?

470
00:29:04.284 --> 00:29:07.412
Uh. no. she's not coming.
She has a meeting.

471
00:29:09.205 --> 00:29:11.332
You sure she's a good influence?

472
00:29:11.416 --> 00:29:14.502
She's part of the reason you
decided to get on that train.

473
00:29:14.586 --> 00:29:18.423
Yeah. but she's not the
one who got on the train.

474
00:29:18.506 --> 00:29:20.508
It still doesn't
answer my question.

475
00:29:25.763 --> 00:29:27.908
You know what I feel like
nobody in my life understands?

476
00:29:27.932 --> 00:29:31.352
Is that like drugs are honestly
the only way I can be myself.

477
00:29:31.436 --> 00:29:33.980
Yeah. I. I don't
think that's true.

478
00:29:34.063 --> 00:29:35.273
Nah. it is true.

479
00:29:35.356 --> 00:29:37.025
Like when I first met you.

480
00:29:37.108 --> 00:29:40.236
I would've never had
the balls to just. like.

481
00:29:40.320 --> 00:29:42.739
- come up to you and talk to you.
- Why?

482
00:29:42.822 --> 00:29:45.700
Rue: I don't know. I'm just
like a deeply shy person.

483
00:29:47.744 --> 00:29:50.580
And like with
Jules. right? Like...

484
00:29:51.706 --> 00:29:54.250
when I first met
her. I was just...

485
00:29:56.252 --> 00:29:58.379
immediately in love.

486
00:30:00.423 --> 00:30:02.634
- In love?
- Rue: Yeah.

487
00:30:03.927 --> 00:30:06.304
When you say it out loud
it kind of sounds small.

488
00:30:07.639 --> 00:30:09.682
Elliot: What's a bigger
feeling than love?

489
00:30:12.894 --> 00:30:14.187
Loss.

490
00:30:15.605 --> 00:30:17.106
Elliot: You think?

491
00:30:18.274 --> 00:30:19.609
Yeah. I think so.

492
00:30:22.487 --> 00:30:24.697
Yeah.

493
00:30:24.781 --> 00:30:26.581
I don't know. Maybe
that's what it was. right?

494
00:30:26.658 --> 00:30:28.409
Like...

495
00:30:28.493 --> 00:30:32.247
as soon as I saw her. I was
just immediately afraid to lose her.

496
00:30:33.248 --> 00:30:34.624
Who have you lost?

497
00:30:35.667 --> 00:30:37.752
Uh. my dad.

498
00:30:37.835 --> 00:30:40.296
- Meaning?
- Meaning he's dead.

499
00:30:42.048 --> 00:30:44.467
Shit. I'm sorry.

500
00:30:44.551 --> 00:30:46.719
It's fine. You
didn't. like. kill him.

501
00:30:46.803 --> 00:30:48.304
How was he killed?

502
00:30:49.597 --> 00:30:51.266
Rue: Oh. he wasn't.

503
00:30:51.349 --> 00:30:53.244
- Are you fucking with me right now?
- (Rue laughs)

504
00:30:53.268 --> 00:30:56.062
Uh. no. it was. it was cancer.

505
00:30:57.564 --> 00:30:58.773
Shit.

506
00:30:59.440 --> 00:31:00.650
(Rue sighs)

507
00:31:00.733 --> 00:31:01.818
Yeah.

508
00:31:03.528 --> 00:31:06.573
- How old were you?
- Rue: I was 14.

509
00:31:06.656 --> 00:31:09.534
- So recently.
- Not really.

510
00:31:10.785 --> 00:31:12.620
Elliot: I feel like
that's kind of recent.

511
00:31:13.663 --> 00:31:16.332
I don't know. I guess.

512
00:31:16.416 --> 00:31:18.835
Honestly it feels like
fuckin' forever ago.

513
00:31:20.837 --> 00:31:22.630
Is that why you
started doing drugs?

514
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:25.675
(chuckles) That's
funny. That's what. uh...

515
00:31:25.758 --> 00:31:28.261
That's what everybody
asks in rehab.

516
00:31:28.344 --> 00:31:30.656
- Elliot: What do you mean?
- Uh. just that. you know. like.

517
00:31:30.680 --> 00:31:33.099
I wish it was that
simple. you know. like...

518
00:31:33.182 --> 00:31:35.643
"Well. my dad died. so
I started doing drugs."

519
00:31:35.727 --> 00:31:37.061
- Elliot: Yeah.
- Yeah.

520
00:31:37.145 --> 00:31:39.480
I feel like everyone's
looking for like a...

521
00:31:39.564 --> 00:31:41.482
cause and effect.

522
00:31:41.566 --> 00:31:43.985
Sometimes shit's
just like is what it is.

523
00:31:44.068 --> 00:31:45.778
Rue: Yeah. exactly.

524
00:31:45.862 --> 00:31:47.488
I don't know.

525
00:31:47.572 --> 00:31:49.449
To be honest. if my
dad was still here.

526
00:31:49.532 --> 00:31:51.409
I'd probably still
be doin' this shit.

527
00:31:53.077 --> 00:31:55.788
(Rue snorts. grunts)

528
00:31:55.872 --> 00:31:58.291
How does Jules not know
that you're doing drugs?

529
00:31:58.374 --> 00:32:01.169
Ugh. 'cause I'm good at my job.

530
00:32:02.587 --> 00:32:05.173
Do you think it's a good
thing that we're friends?

531
00:32:06.424 --> 00:32:07.759
Yeah. why?

532
00:32:08.968 --> 00:32:10.762
I just feel like...

533
00:32:10.845 --> 00:32:14.140
we might not bring out
the best in each other.

534
00:32:17.101 --> 00:32:19.145
I feel like I'm okay with that.

535
00:32:24.817 --> 00:32:26.194
Ethan (on phone): I love you.

536
00:32:26.277 --> 00:32:28.905
- I love you.
- Ethan: I love you more.

537
00:32:28.988 --> 00:32:30.573
I love you more than more.

538
00:32:32.367 --> 00:32:35.745
- (hangs up) -
(groans) My god. no.

539
00:32:35.828 --> 00:32:37.664
(video plays on computer)

540
00:32:37.747 --> 00:32:41.000
Rue: Ethan made plans with
Kat to go bowling that night.

541
00:32:41.084 --> 00:32:43.252
Kat was depressed because
she couldn't figure out why

542
00:32:43.336 --> 00:32:45.380
she didn't love Ethan.

543
00:32:45.463 --> 00:32:49.217
So she decided to make
a list of pros and cons.

544
00:33:01.479 --> 00:33:03.940
♪ ♪

545
00:33:08.653 --> 00:33:10.488
But she couldn't
think of anything.

546
00:33:10.571 --> 00:33:13.408
which made her realize
Ethan might not be the problem.

547
00:33:13.491 --> 00:33:15.660
Mmm. (imitates gunshot)

548
00:33:17.328 --> 00:33:18.955
(video playing)

549
00:33:19.038 --> 00:33:21.416
Rue Kat hated herself.

550
00:33:21.499 --> 00:33:24.711
But the problem with hating
yourself is you can't really talk about it.

551
00:33:24.794 --> 00:33:26.421
Because at some point recently.

552
00:33:26.504 --> 00:33:28.172
the whole world
joined a self-help cult

553
00:33:28.256 --> 00:33:29.799
and won't shut
the fuck up about it.

554
00:33:29.882 --> 00:33:32.260
It's not gonna solve
all your life problems.

555
00:33:32.343 --> 00:33:33.845
but it is gonna solve...

556
00:33:33.928 --> 00:33:35.638
Influencer: Kat.

557
00:33:35.722 --> 00:33:36.931
You're one of the bravest.

558
00:33:37.014 --> 00:33:38.683
most beautiful human beings

559
00:33:38.766 --> 00:33:40.435
I have ever seen.

560
00:33:40.518 --> 00:33:43.980
- (mouth full) That's not true.
- Yes. it is.

561
00:33:44.063 --> 00:33:46.357
I wish I had your confidence.

562
00:33:46.441 --> 00:33:49.402
But I don't. like...
feel healthy.

563
00:33:49.485 --> 00:33:50.903
Yes. you are.

564
00:33:50.987 --> 00:33:54.532
No. like... seriously. I'm not.

565
00:33:54.615 --> 00:33:57.160
Kat. you just have
to love yourself.

566
00:33:57.243 --> 00:33:59.036
Kat: But that's what
I'm trying to tell you!

567
00:33:59.120 --> 00:34:01.414
I fucking hate myself!

568
00:34:01.497 --> 00:34:04.459
Every day you get out of bed...

569
00:34:04.542 --> 00:34:06.043
It's an act of courage.

570
00:34:06.127 --> 00:34:07.211
That's easy for you to say.

571
00:34:07.295 --> 00:34:09.255
You don't have like
fucking mental problems.

572
00:34:09.338 --> 00:34:12.717
Yes. I do. Why do you
think I look like this?

573
00:34:12.800 --> 00:34:14.135
Are you kidding?

574
00:34:14.217 --> 00:34:16.471
I wish my mental problems
made me look like you.

575
00:34:16.554 --> 00:34:18.556
- Trust me. you don't.
- Kat: Trust me. I do!

576
00:34:18.639 --> 00:34:21.034
You're like the most beautiful
person I've ever fucking seen.

577
00:34:21.058 --> 00:34:24.395
Maybe by a white. cis-male.
heteronormative standard.

578
00:34:24.478 --> 00:34:26.938
Oh my god. Are
you fucking joking?!

579
00:34:27.023 --> 00:34:28.775
(yells) Kat! Are you
fucking serious?!

580
00:34:28.858 --> 00:34:31.152
That's not you fucking
talking! It's the patriarchy!

581
00:34:31.235 --> 00:34:34.112
It is me talking!
You are not listening!

582
00:34:34.197 --> 00:34:36.282
No! Society puts
things into your mind!

583
00:34:36.364 --> 00:34:39.952
I don't care about
society! I feel like shit!

584
00:34:40.036 --> 00:34:43.080
Kat. you need to smash
all beauty standards.

585
00:34:43.164 --> 00:34:44.998
But I can't even get out of bed!

586
00:34:45.081 --> 00:34:46.458
You have to love yourself.

587
00:34:46.542 --> 00:34:48.262
You need to find your
inner fuckin' warrior!

588
00:34:48.293 --> 00:34:51.130
- Become a bad bitch.
- Just like you did last year.

589
00:34:51.214 --> 00:34:54.342
- But that wasn't even real.
- It looked real.

590
00:34:54.425 --> 00:34:56.803
- Kat: That was the point!
- I found it inspiring.

591
00:34:56.886 --> 00:35:01.349
- Shut the fuck up!
- Group (chanting): Love yourself! Love yourself!

592
00:35:01.432 --> 00:35:03.851
Love yourself! Love yourself!

593
00:35:03.935 --> 00:35:08.940
(Kat shouts) Leave me
alone! Get the fuck out!

594
00:35:09.023 --> 00:35:13.653
(shouting. chanting continue)

595
00:35:13.736 --> 00:35:15.112
(phone chimes)

596
00:35:20.910 --> 00:35:22.370
(chanting stops)

597
00:35:25.540 --> 00:35:26.540
Fuck.

598
00:35:26.582 --> 00:35:27.625
(phone buzzes)

599
00:35:28.876 --> 00:35:30.169
Hey.

600
00:35:31.462 --> 00:35:36.134
Uh. nothing just...
depressed in the bath.

601
00:35:39.428 --> 00:35:40.972
Bowling?

602
00:35:41.055 --> 00:35:44.141
("She Brings the
Rain" by Can playing)

603
00:35:44.225 --> 00:35:47.645
♪ ♪

604
00:35:59.448 --> 00:36:02.869
♪ Yes. I care if she
brings me spring ♪

605
00:36:02.952 --> 00:36:05.204
♪ But don't care about nothing ♪

606
00:36:05.288 --> 00:36:07.498
Rue: What the fuck?

607
00:36:08.541 --> 00:36:10.751
♪ She brings the rain ♪

608
00:36:10.835 --> 00:36:13.671
♪ Oh yeah. she brings the rain ♪

609
00:36:13.754 --> 00:36:17.592
♪ ♪

610
00:36:17.675 --> 00:36:21.262
♪ In the dawn of
the silvery day ♪

611
00:36:21.345 --> 00:36:22.471
(line ringing)

612
00:36:22.555 --> 00:36:26.601
♪ Clouds seem to melt away ♪

613
00:36:26.684 --> 00:36:28.769
♪ She brings the rain ♪

614
00:36:28.853 --> 00:36:32.315
♪ Oh yeah. she brings the rain ♪

615
00:36:35.776 --> 00:36:39.572
♪ She brings the rain.
it feels like spring ♪

616
00:36:39.655 --> 00:36:41.908
Nate (on voicemail):
Yo. this is Nate. I'm busy.

617
00:36:41.991 --> 00:36:43.784
Leave a message at the beep.

618
00:36:43.868 --> 00:36:44.911
(beeps)

619
00:36:44.994 --> 00:36:47.622
♪ She brings the rain ♪

620
00:36:47.705 --> 00:36:49.957
♪ Oh yeah. she brings the rain ♪

621
00:36:50.041 --> 00:36:51.584
(phone buzzes)

622
00:36:54.086 --> 00:36:58.799
♪ She brings the rain.
it feels like spring ♪

623
00:36:58.883 --> 00:37:02.929
♪ Magic mushrooms
out of things ♪

624
00:37:03.012 --> 00:37:11.012
♪ She brings the rain.
it feels like spring ♪

625
00:37:16.233 --> 00:37:18.736
♪ She brings the rain ♪

626
00:37:18.819 --> 00:37:20.905
♪ ♪

627
00:37:29.246 --> 00:37:31.082
(grunts)

628
00:37:37.713 --> 00:37:39.340
(whirring)

629
00:37:46.472 --> 00:37:47.848
(sighs)

630
00:37:49.684 --> 00:37:51.936
Look who the cat dragged in.

631
00:37:52.895 --> 00:37:54.605
Yeah. yeah.

632
00:37:57.566 --> 00:38:00.695
(whispers): I see you're
still on your suicide mission.

633
00:38:02.738 --> 00:38:06.117
Let go. Let God.

634
00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:12.289
(Ali sighs)

635
00:38:19.839 --> 00:38:22.049
Where are we goin'?

636
00:38:31.350 --> 00:38:33.811
(inaudible)

637
00:38:33.894 --> 00:38:35.980
