685
00:43:18.596 --> 00:43:20.222
Cass!

686
00:43:24.977 --> 00:43:26.520
Cassie!

687
00:43:35.571 --> 00:43:37.156
Nate: Cassie!

688
00:43:38.282 --> 00:43:40.117
Cassie!

689
00:43:44.413 --> 00:43:46.999
(airplane flying overhead)

690
00:44:20.157 --> 00:44:22.659
(melancholy music playing)

691
00:44:22.743 --> 00:44:24.828
♪ ♪

692
00:44:55.567 --> 00:44:58.445
Nate: You don't know
how much power you have.

693
00:44:59.113 --> 00:45:00.239
(kissing)

694
00:45:00.322 --> 00:45:01.532
(Cassie moans)

695
00:45:02.366 --> 00:45:03.867
Nate (quietly): Fuck.

696
00:45:18.090 --> 00:45:21.385
How are you ever gonna
look Maddy in the eye again?

697
00:45:27.307 --> 00:45:30.936
Feel sorry I didn't get to
say goodbye on New Year's.

698
00:45:31.019 --> 00:45:32.271
Good evening.

699
00:45:33.522 --> 00:45:35.274
(tense music playing)

700
00:45:35.357 --> 00:45:36.859
What's up. man?

701
00:45:40.529 --> 00:45:43.449
♪ ♪

702
00:45:59.882 --> 00:46:01.300
You got any spearmint gum?

703
00:46:01.383 --> 00:46:04.511
I don't know. man.
The gum's right here.

704
00:46:08.515 --> 00:46:10.601
♪ ♪

705
00:46:15.063 --> 00:46:17.357
This your store?

706
00:46:17.441 --> 00:46:19.234
It's a family business.

707
00:46:21.612 --> 00:46:23.489
Cal: Do your parents own it?

708
00:46:23.572 --> 00:46:25.407
(bag crinkling)

709
00:46:29.411 --> 00:46:31.955
You usually ask this
many questions. man?

710
00:46:37.294 --> 00:46:38.545
Just you.

711
00:46:41.924 --> 00:46:43.967
She tell you who I am?

712
00:46:47.137 --> 00:46:50.599
- Nah. man.
- Faye: Are you a cop?

713
00:46:53.060 --> 00:46:54.144
No.

714
00:46:55.771 --> 00:47:03.771
♪ ♪

715
00:47:33.642 --> 00:47:35.894
Just a concerned father.

716
00:47:44.194 --> 00:47:48.865
(car door closes. engine starts)

717
00:47:57.833 --> 00:48:00.127
(lights flickering)

718
00:48:01.545 --> 00:48:04.172
(pop music playing on speakers)

719
00:48:06.758 --> 00:48:09.553
You know what's
kind of depressing?

720
00:48:09.636 --> 00:48:13.932
- What?
- I'll never find that kind of love.

721
00:48:14.808 --> 00:48:16.435
What do you mean?

722
00:48:16.518 --> 00:48:20.689
There's just no
darkness. It's just sweet.

723
00:48:21.690 --> 00:48:23.442
Jules: Yeah.

724
00:48:23.525 --> 00:48:25.986
I don't know if that would
ever be enough for me.

725
00:48:28.614 --> 00:48:30.741
I don't know... I mean.

726
00:48:30.824 --> 00:48:34.870
I guess some people are
just kinda built different.

727
00:48:38.248 --> 00:48:39.541
Yeah.

728
00:48:41.418 --> 00:48:42.919
Guess so.

729
00:48:46.006 --> 00:48:48.925
All: It works if you work it.

730
00:48:49.926 --> 00:48:51.928
(applause)

731
00:48:53.555 --> 00:48:55.158
How 'bout you let me
give you a ride home?

732
00:48:55.182 --> 00:48:57.517
Um. I'm okay. I
got my. uh. my bike.

733
00:48:57.601 --> 00:49:00.979
Yeah. yeah. I'm not sure you should
be behind the handlebars right now.

734
00:49:01.063 --> 00:49:04.566
("Blue Monk" by
Thelonious Monk playing)

735
00:49:07.235 --> 00:49:10.238
- Yo. you ever listen to Thelonious Monk?
- No.

736
00:49:10.322 --> 00:49:11.448
- (scoffs)
- What?

737
00:49:11.531 --> 00:49:13.825
Greatest jazz
pianist who ever lived.

738
00:49:13.909 --> 00:49:16.620
Supposedly. he had huge hands.

739
00:49:16.703 --> 00:49:18.163
He would play like this.

740
00:49:18.246 --> 00:49:20.749
and then he would
roll his hands over.

741
00:49:20.832 --> 00:49:22.751
hit the keys... (fades out)

742
00:49:22.834 --> 00:49:25.921
♪ ♪

743
00:49:34.304 --> 00:49:36.014
(turns off engine)

744
00:49:36.098 --> 00:49:39.309
- All right.
- Okay. what are you doing?

745
00:49:39.393 --> 00:49:42.062
I'm gonna introduce
myself to your mother.

746
00:49:42.145 --> 00:49:45.524
- What are you talkin' about?
- Rue. if my daughter was gettin' rides home from NA

747
00:49:45.607 --> 00:49:48.068
